edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.meta.parameters

Class ParameterDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.meta.parameters.ParameterDictionary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ParameterDictionary
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Represents a set of String keys, and associated parameter objects that specify various parameters for the analysis and their values.
    Author:
    Colin J. Fuller

      • getValueForKey

        public String getValueForKey(String key)
        Gets the value stored for a given key. Returns null, as per the specification in java.util.Hashtable if there is no value for key stored.
        Parameters:
        key - The key whose associated value is to be returned.
        Returns:
        The corresponding value, in String format.

      • getValueForKey

        public String getValueForKey(String key,
                    int i)
        Gets the ith value stored for a given key. Does not check bounds, so check the number of values stored using getValueCountForKey(String) beforehand.
        Parameters:
        key - The key whose associated value is to be returned.
        i - The index of the value associated with this key to return.
        Returns:
        The value of the parameter as a String, or null if there is no value stored.

        Parameters:
        key - The key whose associated value is to be returned.
        i - The index of the value associated with this key to return.
        Returns:
        The Parameter object associated with the key, or null if there is no value stored.

      • hasKeyAndTrue

        public boolean hasKeyAndTrue(String key)
        Convenience method for checking if the ParameterDictionary has a key and that the corresponding value is true.

      • addIfNotSet

        public void addIfNotSet(String key,
               String value)
        Adds a key, value pair to the ParameterDictionary. Does nothing if the specified key already has an associated value. This method is useful for setting up default values after parsing user-specified options, as the defaults will not overwrite the existing values.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to add to the ParameterDictionary if it is not present.
        value - The key's associated String value. A new Parameter object will be constructed.

      • addIfNotSet

        public void addIfNotSet(String key,
               Parameter value)
        Adds a key, value pair to the ParameterDictionary. Does nothing if the specified key already has an associated value. This method is useful for setting up default values after parsing user-specified options, as the defaults will not overwrite the existing values.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to add to the ParameterDictionary if it is not present.
        value - The key's associated Parameter.

      • discardIllegalArguments

        public void discardIllegalArguments(String[] legalArguments)
        Removes all key,value pairs from the ParameterDictionary that are not listed in a specified array of valid keys.
        Parameters:
        legalArguments - A String array containing the valid keys; any key, value pair not matching one of these keys will be discarded.

      • hasKey

        public boolean hasKey(String key)
        Checks if the ParameterDictionary contains a specified key.
        Parameters:
        key - A String that is the key to check for in this ParameterDictionary.
        Returns:
        A boolean corresponding to whether the specified key has an associated value.

      • setValueForKey

        public void setValueForKey(String key,
                  String value)
        Adds a key, value pair to the ParameterDictionary. This is distinct from addIfNotSet(String, String) in that this method will overwrite any existing value.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to add to the ParameterDictionary.
        value - The value associated with the key, which will overwrite any existing value.

      • addValueForKey

        public void addValueForKey(String key,
                  Parameter value)
        Adds a key, value pair to the ParameterDictionary. This is distinct from addIfNotSet(String, String) in that this method will add an additional value for a key if there is one already present.
        Parameters:
        key - The key to add to the ParameterDictionary.
        value - The Parameter associated with the key
